# ADR 0001: adopt clap for arg parsing
## Context
hello-world hand-rolls std::env::args(); adding --greeting and future flags is fragile.
## Decision
Adopt the clap crate for declarative arg parsing.
## Status
Proposed.
## Consequences
Pro: declarative flags, --help/validation for free. Trade-off: adds a dependency (clap +
its transitive deps), increases binary size (~300KB) and compile time; the toy is no longer
dependency-free. Locks us to clap's release cadence.
## Alternatives
(1) keep hand-rolled parsing — zero deps but manual --help; (2) lexopt — lighter than clap
but fewer features. Chose clap for ergonomics despite the dependency cost.
